programme.title: Dealers Put Your Money Where Your Mouth Is
programme.desc: Some people play the lottery, others dream of unearthing a valuable antique treasure at Saturday morning garage sales. Your odds of achieving the latter may improve drastically thanks to this series that asks expert antiques dealers to reveal their secrets of turning trash to treasure as they are challenged to put their money where their mouth is. Each episode, two expert antiques dealers are given a budget and challenged to find and purchase overlooked treasures at various flea markets. At the end of their shopping spree, their loot is sent to auction. The dealer who walks away with the most profit reigns supreme.

programme.title: In Bruges
programme.desc: Oscar-winning writer/director Martin McDonagh makes his feature directorial debut with this story of a life-and-death struggle of darkly comic proportions starring Colin Farrell and Brendan Gleeson. Bruges is a welcoming destination for travellers, but for hit men Ray (Farrell) and Ken (Gleeson) it could be their final destination. Ralph Fiennes stars as their boss Harry, who orders the pair out of London after a difficult job. He suggests they go and cool their heels in the storybook Flemish city for a couple of weeks. The two hit men fill their days living the lives of tourists. Still haunted by the London job, Ray hates the place, while Ken, even as he keeps a fatherly eye on Ray's often profanely funny exploits, finds his mind and soul being expanded by the beauty and serenity of the city. But the longer they stay waiting for Harry's call, the more surreal their experience becomes, as they find themselves in weird encounters with locals, tourists, violent medieval art, a dwarf American actor (Jordan Prentice) shooting a European art film, Dutch prostitutes, and a potential romance for Ray in the form of Chloe (Clemence Poesy), who may have some dark secrets of her own.

programme.desc: By all appearances, new parents Mac and Kelly Radner are living the American Dream - complete with an adorable baby girl and a beautiful new starter home in the suburbs. Still, the early-thirtysomethings want to believe that they have a modicum of coolness left within them. So when they discover that their new next-door neighbours are none other than dozens of Delta Psi Beta fraternity brothers led by charismatic president Teddy Sanders, they try to play along and make the best of an awkward situation. programme.title: In Bruges
programme.desc: Oscar-winning writer/director Martin McDonagh makes his feature directorial debut with this story of a life-and-death struggle of darkly comic proportions starring Colin Farrell and Brendan Gleeson. Bruges is a welcoming destination for travellers, but for hit men Ray (Farrell) and Ken (Gleeson) it could be their final destination. Ralph Fiennes stars as their boss Harry, who orders the pair out of London after a difficult job. He suggests they go and cool their heels in the storybook Flemish city for a couple of weeks. The two hit men fill their days living the lives of tourists. Still haunted by the London job, Ray hates the place, while Ken, even as he keeps a fatherly eye on Ray's often profanely funny exploits, finds his mind and soul being expanded by the beauty and serenity of the city. But the longer they stay waiting for Harry's call, the more surreal their experience becomes, as they find themselves in weird encounters with locals, tourists, violent medieval art, a dwarf American actor (Jordan Prentice) shooting a European art film, Dutch prostitutes, and a potential romance for Ray in the form of Chloe (Clemence Poesy), who may have some dark secrets of her own.

programme.desc: Follow the adventures, trials and tribulations of Dominic "The Dom", owner of a fleet of six shrimp boats in the Gulf of Mexico, and his crew of shrimpers from Alabama. programme.title: Locked Up Abroad
programme.desc: British gay nurse Stephen Comiskey has had a difficult year. He's come out about his sexuality and left his wife and children. Needing to support his family, he takes a high-paying nursing job in Saudi Arabia. When he discovers that homosexuality is punishable by death, he decides to be celibate. His resolve weakens however, when he learns there is a thriving gay scene there. He embarks on a series of secret affairs and thinks he can get away with it until one night he is beaten up by the religious police and thrown into jail.

programme.title: Mighty Planes
programme.desc: We go behind the scenes as one of Omega's 707 Tankers takes part in FIREX - a three-day live fire operation over the deserts of Southern California. Its job is to refuel thirsty F/A-18 Hornets and Harrier jets participating in the manoeuvres. Nerves of steel, sharp eyes and a steady hand are essential for pilots aboard both the 707 Tanker and the receiver jets. Turbulence, wing-tip vortices, and human error - all could spell disaster in a heartbeat.

programme.title: Mighty Planes
programme.desc: NOAA's two P-3 turboprop aircraft, Kermit and Miss Piggy, have been battle tested through over 100 hurricanes and every year they're ready to take on more. Working in tandem with a twin engine Gulfstream IV jet (Gonzo), these are no ordinary aircraft but flying laboratories, equipped with an arsenal of data sensors, airborne radars, cloud physics instruments, dropsondes, and an aircraft-satellite data link that transmits information to the National Hurricane Centre.

programme.title: Mighty Planes
programme.desc: In this episode we'll fly with Donald Trump and his flight crew on a transatlantic mission to the UK for a speech and pit-stop at his new golf course in Scotland. Fog, runway curfews, security sweeps and a missing engine cowling are just some of the challenges threatening the jet's upcoming flight as Commander Dunkin races against time to get 'The Donald' to his destination on time and in style.

programme.title: Mudcats
programme.desc: Along Oklahoma's many rivers, a group of daring men practise a tradition dating back to early pioneer days, catching giant catfish with nothing more than their bare hands. Catfish "noodling"is a way to supplement incomes during the regulated catfish season. The colourful characters who practice it brave snakes, bugs, riptides, and more, reaching into muddy waters, using their fingers as bait for giant fish that weigh up to 30 pounds. This series will celebrate this uniquely all-American tradition while showing the little-known world of Mudcatters.

programme.title: Big Shrimpin'
programme.desc: Follow the adventures, trials and tribulations of Dominic "The Dom", owner of a fleet of six shrimp boats in the Gulf of Mexico, and his crew of shrimpers from Alabama. They have 30 days across June and July to make their money by scouring the Gulf, looking for the best territory to drag their heavy funnel-shaped trawl nets over the sea floor like a mule pulling a plow. Shrimping has been part of the Gulf since the 17th century when fisherman used vertical nets up to 600 feet in diameter to scoop up the delicacy. With the invention of the flat bottom "otter trawl"along with motorised engines, the territory and depth of shrimping expanded. Currently the US harvests over half million pounds of shrimp and imports another 200 million pounds a year, more than any other country. The competition is fierce among Dom's boats, each crew working hard to bring in the biggest haul for the biggest payday. Travel with the Shrimpers as they battle each other, the weather and crew from other companies.

programme.title: Outback Hunters
programme.desc: In the desolate northern territory of the Australian Outback lies a vast wilderness called Kakadu, roamed by the Aborigines for 40,000 years and bordered by three rivers, the East, West and South Alligator Rivers. This part of the Outback has attracted the most extreme of characters for centuries. In the 1800s bushrangers, English prisoners with the best survival skills, escaped from city prisons and made this part of the country their new stomping grounds. But it wasn't the escaped convicts that struck fear into the locals; it was and still is, the "Salties", the massive saltwater crocodiles known as the biggest, baddest reptiles on the planet. This adrenaline-filled series follows a team of charismatic Aussies, as they manage and cull this highly protected species. Brave hunters cull the predators during a legitimate annual hunting season. The truly daring help manage the population by capturing prized croc eggs, swooping down on nests from helicopters flown by bush pilots.

Midsomer's new detective DCI John Barnaby also makes an appearance. In Fit For Murder, Barnaby reluctantly accompanies Joyce on a spa weekend to upmarket Swavely Manor. But as he attempts to de-stress amid the New Age therapies, a woman is found dead in the floatation chamber. Abandoning the treatments to investigate, Barnaby uncovers a feud between neighbours, money wrangles and the mystery of a half-written novel. But, despite the distractions of the case, Barnaby has a birthday approaching and a decision to make. His personal worries are never far from the surface.

programme.title: Who's Been Sleeping In My House
programme.desc: Invercloy is a grand Federation-style home in Redcliffe, Western Australia where it stands out as a majestic mansion in a sea of suburbia. But beyond the house's visual charm, George and Pauline Christidis reckon Invercloy spins a special magic, which they can't explain. Prior to moving in two years ago, life with their four young boys was rowdy to say the least. But when they arrived at Invercloy, something short of a miracle occurred - the bickering and fighting stopped and peace descended for the first time. There's no doubt the big, rambling house afforded some breathing room for the boisterous brothers, but Pauline is convinced that the house exudes something more. Her question: what could be behind Invercloy's spell that has worked such wonders on her family? That's not the only question that hangs in the air for Adam Ford. The family is also convinced they share Invercloy's corridors with a ghostly presence, and it doesn't take long for Adam to corroborate many other tales of supposed sightings. Finally, wine lover George has a question that's more down to earth. He's heard stories that Invercloy was legendary for its hunting parties in the early twentieth century, and the thirsty guests were well serviced by the house's extensive wine cellars. But the cellars haven't been seen for 60 years, and George is keen to know if they ever existed, and if so, where they could be.

programme.title: Waybuloo
programme.desc: Discover that 'everything is better together' in Waybuloo. Waybuloo transports children into a magical land called Nara : a world inhabited by adorable animated characters called Piplings. Taking a completely original approach, Waybuloo focuses on children's feelings, and the Piplings embody a range of emotions including love, wisdom, happiness and harmony : all in search of 'Waybuloo'. Piplings are joyful and gentle creatures who personify positive emotion through the natural ability to float when they're happy. They have a childlike innocence and sense of wonder, making them inquisitive, impulsive and funny. Naturally selfless, thoughtful and sweet-natured, they take care in their relationships with each other and the world. In each episode, six children visit Nara to play with the Piplings and explore their land, as real life interacts with the animated world, showing that every child can visit Nara and find their own Waybuloo. Episode One: De Li stands on a box to reach some plumatoes on a tree. Having picked the fruit, she takes the box to her pod. But when she gets back from Yogo, the box has gone! It turns out that each Pipling is 'borrowing' the box for his or her own needs. Episode Two: Showtime : Saturday December 05 at 11:00am Lau Lau is planning a big show. She gathers everyone at Yo Jojo's performance area and does her dance. The others are so impressed, they join in! But their moves aren't right : and worse : they're taking the limelight away from Lau Lau

programme.title: Chuggington
programme.desc: Chuggington follows the adventures of three young trainee trains, Wilson, Brewster and Koko as they learn to ride the rails. Their 'training time' provides the storylines and echoes the experience of every pre-school age child as they too take their first steps into the world. The community refers to the trains as 'chuggers'. The trains talk, think for themselves and don't need drivers. This series features chuggers from all around the world, whether diesel, electric, steam, or high-speed and they all live and work in Chuggington. Ep 1 - Can't Catch Koko When Harrison breaks down, Koko volunteers to replace him on the night shift, determined to make the fastest run ever. But Vee insists that Wilson and Brewster go too, despite Koko's protests that Brewster will slow them down. Koko races off, teasing Brewster about being a 'slowcoach.' Suddenly Koko shudders and slows down to a stop and the others are nowhere to be seen. Chuggington will be repeated on ABC2 - Thursday, February 19 at 12:45pm

programme.title: In The Night Garden
programme.desc: In the Night Garden is about a magical picture-book place that exists between waking and sleeping in a child's imagination. Reached by following a magical little blue star, the Night Garden is a warm and affectionate world which is home to a comical and diverse community of toys, living happily together, and who care for each other unconditionally. In the Night Garden is a thoroughly modern interpretation of a nursery rhyme picture book, and takes children on an imaginative journey to meet a host of wonderfully silly characters living together within a happy and caring community. It is both funny and reassuring, with a capacity to relax and entertain. The tone of the program is deliberately literary. Words, rhymes and music carry the viewer through a happy world of loveable characters and nursery rhyme nonsense. Filmed in real woodland, the setting is breathtaking and the program weaves together the very latest technical innovations in live-character costume technology and computer animation, to create a compelling and fully immersing experience for young viewers.

programme.title: Highway Thru Hell
programme.desc: In the rugged mountains of British Columbia in Canada, there's a highway like no other. An unforgiving, white-knuckle ride that thousands of truckers must run every day. Keeping the Coquihalla Highway open takes an army of men and machines and the last line of defense is the fleet of Jamie Davis Heavy Rescue. Jamie's team is willing to tackle any disaster the mountain throws at them. They have been entrusted to keep some of the most economically important and inhospitable roads in Canada open and safe during the winter season. The stakes are high - lives, the economy and thousands of jobs depend on the highways staying clear, but the extreme mountain roads are fraught with steep, icy terrain where Mother Nature reigns supreme. During winter storms truckers crash and close the road every twelve hours on average and when they do, the call goes out to the team of heavy rescue tow truck drivers who are on call 24/7. Even the toughest men in the towing business are pushed to breaking point; they have witnessed some horrific scenes. The drivers must brave the extreme temperatures and seemingly impossible conditions to remove often dangerous cargo, clean up the carnage and get the truck traffic rolling again. Fast.

Jamie's team is willing to tackle any disaster the mountain throws at them. They have been entrusted to keep some of the most economically important and inhospitable roads in Canada open and safe during the winter season. The stakes are high - lives, the economy and thousands of jobs depend on the highways staying clear, but the extreme mountain roads are fraught with steep, icy terrain where Mother Nature reigns supreme. Cosmo, Rowan, Hayden, Jake, Molly and Mia are fresh, funny, unpredictable and different and give the series its innovative, edgy appeal. During the series, the ABC3 audience is introduced to characters such as Tattiana the Sailor Girl, Voldemort, Internet Speak Girl, Mario and Luigi, Cavemen, Vikings, Naughty Girl Guides, Bear Cub, the Hipsters, Uncle Vijay, Inappropriate Joe, the Australia's Next Big Talent judges and the accident prone Helmet Boy. The series also features regular animated segments with characters such as Vomit Boy and his faithful assistant Kayne, Barry and Chuck the tomatoes, Ned the panda, and Rex the dinosaur. You're Skitting Me was written by a combination of some of Australia's most experienced comedy writers including Mark O'Toole and Ray Matsen along with some of the newest rising-star writers and a cast who were encouraged to develop their writing skills with a mentor program designed to find the next generation of comic writers. Episode one: Wednesday, February 29 at 7.30am The first episode of You're Skitting Me features skits on Twilight and Australia's Next Big Talent competition. Uncle Vijay is introduced and provides commentary on the latest television shows and also takes a look at cavemen times to see what new and amazing ideas are being discussed. Jacob the child superstar tries to make a comeback; two BFF's go through some good and bad times; the kids of Jolimont High Witness News take a look at detention; Superhero Vomit Boy takes on his latest adventure and Barry and Chuck, the tomatoes, argue over the small things in life. Episode two: Thursday, March 1 at 7.30am This episode introduces Mario and his faithful assistant Luigi into the world outside of their computer game; two naughty girl guides try to earn their 'Being Helpful' badges, the first instalment of 'Viking High', Voldemort tries to win a board game, resident safety girl Maive Blairs lays out the rules, and Rex the dinosaur takes on his bullies in a running race.

programme.title: Tropic Thunder
programme.desc: Rookie director Damien Cockburn (Steve Coogan) has been given the thankless task of shooting the studio's latest big budget film - a Vietnam war adventure. Between the acting difficulties of his lead, Tugg Speedman (Ben Stiller), the egos of Kirk Lazarus (Robert Downey Jr) a "serious" Australian method actor, and Jeff Portnoy (Jack Black), an obnoxious star with an addiction to more than sugar - and a studio head (Tom Cruise) who thinks he's totally incompetent - Damien has is work cut out for him. At his wits end, he takes advice from the author of the book on which the film is based - "Four Leaf" Tayback (Nick Nolte): he takes his stars out into the jungle, and drops them - no phones, no food, no escape. His plan is to shoot the action sequences live. However, Damien has unwittingly dropped them in the middle of Asia's golden triangle: the prime heroin production area, controlled by gangsters. Tuggman is taken prisoner - and it is up to his fellow actors to man up and come up with a plan to save him - and themselves.

programme.title: Jila
programme.sub-title: Painted Waters Of The Great Sandy
programme.desc: The Ngurrara people know their desert country - it's where they grew up. But to claim their native title they need to show their knowledge and ownership of the land in a way that makes sense to them and the visiting Native Title Tribunal. They decide to paint their country - on a massive scale. Seventy artists set to work on a specially made canvas measuring eight by ten metres. The richness, complexity and energy of desert life are intertwined with this creative process and the story of the Ngurrara Native Title claim itself. The film culminates in the painting's first journey to Canberra. It goes on display while adults and children sing and dance around it in celebration of their country and in anticipation of claiming it back.

They have shared their cultural performances and stories with wider audiences and this year plan to undertake a tour to several destinations on mainland Australia. What's in store for a group of young people who are now realising their cultural past holds the key to their very modern future? The Torres Strait is home to the Porumagul people of the Kulkulgal nation. This community is one of the smallest in the Torres Strait, and is keenly aware of the problems facing many Indigenous communities in Australia in their loss of cultural identity and tradition. In the past, Elders have been the cornerstone in maintaining the teaching and practice of traditional and cultural knowledge; but recently an unexpected social shift has occurred in some communities whereby the young people have become the proactive element within those roles.

programme.title: Uninhabited
programme.desc: Geraldine Hakewill and Henry James star in this Australian horror thriller inspired by a terrifying true story about a young couple holidaying on a deserted island, where they begin to find evidence of an intruder around their retreat, who seems to resent their presence. Adventurous young lovers Harry (Henry James) and Beth (Geraldine Hakewill) excitedly travel to their remote holiday destination, a deserted island which will contain just the two of them for ten days. As they settle in for a romantic sojourn together, everything seems idyllic until several incidents begin to unsettle them. The couple's belongings are rifled through, and they discover a grave adjacent to an abandoned hut, which contains a journal detailing other people's visits to the island, which were affected by the presence of something, or someone, sinister. Finally, Beth and Harry discover footprints that are not theirs. With their fear growing, they see a person standing out on the reef, and attempt to call the island manager to come to collect them, but the menacing presence, who seems determined to get rid of them, has other plans for the two castaways.

programme.title: The Mysterious Cities Of Gold
programme.desc: The year is 1532. Esteban, a young boy, is told that he was saved by Mendoza, a navigator on a Spanish ship from a ship wreck in a storm at sea. The only clue to his identity is a medal that Esteban wears about his neck. Esteban joins Mendoza on a trip from Spain to the new world - the Americas - where on route he meets two other children - Zia - an Inca girl and Tao, the last member of a highly advanced race. All three are looking for different things - Esteban to find his father and his identity, Zia for her father and Tao for remains of his race. The clues for all three quests however all point to the seven Cities of Gold and so the children, Mendoza, Sancho and Pedro - two other sailors and friends of Mendoza start searching in a massive treasure hunt for the Cities Of Gold...

programme.desc: In their most adventurous, far-flung road trip yet, the Hairy Bikers are touring the birthplaces of their favourite Asian cuisines. In the first episode, they head to Hong Kong. They discover the secrets of wok chi when theyre thrown in at the deep end stir-frying on one of the citys street food stalls. programme.title: The Island With Bear Grylls
programme.desc: Generations of men have wondered if they could survive on a desert island. This new six-part series makes this challenge a reality for 13 ordinary British men. Bear Grylls sets up the ultimate survival experiment to discover if the average modern man is tough and resourceful enough to survive on a remote, uninhabited Pacific island for a month. These 13 men are left completely alone, with only the clothes they stand up in and some basic tools, filming the entire experience themselves with no camera crew. programme.title: Can We Control Gravity?
programme.desc: Scientists have been fascinated with the idea of controlling gravity for over 200 years. In the mid-1990s, British aerospace manufacturer BAE Systems began a ground-breaking project code-named 'Greenglow', which set about turning science fiction into reality. NASA was simultaneously running its own Breakthrough Propulsion Physics Project. Looking at these past projects and into the future, BBC's Horizon explores science's obsession with the idea of gravity control. Are flying cars and journeys to the stars still the stuff of dreams?

programme.title: Bronson
programme.desc: "In introducing himself, Michael "Charles Bronson" Peterson (Tom Hardy) tells his audience that he sought fame from an early age, but did not have conventional talents. It is soon apparent that his talent lies in other areas, as he takes on a number of prison guards in a cage fight. Peterson's early life is shown in flashback, as his violent tendencies begin to surface at school. At the age of 19, his robbery of a post office sends him to prison for seven years, where he comes into his psychopathic element. Creating constant havoc by starting fights with prison officers sees Peterson shunted around various prisons and eventually a psychiatric hospital. He is eventually paroled, and starts boxing, taking on the stage name of Charles Bronson. Inevitably, Bronson ends up back in prison, and notches up 30 years in solitary confinement, which only heightens his distorted and evil take on reality, and ensures his infamy instead of fame."

programme.desc: This documentary uncovers the extraordinary story behind one of the ancient worlds most iconic images. The blue-crowned statue of a beautiful woman, wearing the full regalia of a royal wife was officially dug out of the Amarna desert in 1912. Since that time, admirers have marvelled not only at its artistry, but at its remarkable preservation: the fact that something so delicate could have survived, virtually pristine, for three and a half thousand years. This program traces the history of the bust, and the woman behind it. Egyptologists Jacquelyn Williamson and Barry Kemp reveal Queen Nefertiti as the most powerful woman that Egypt had known. programme.title: Can We Control Gravity?
programme.desc: Scientists have been fascinated with the idea of controlling gravity for over 200 years. In the mid-1990s, British aerospace manufacturer BAE Systems began a ground-breaking project code-named 'Greenglow', which set about turning science fiction into reality. NASA was simultaneously running its own Breakthrough Propulsion Physics Project. Looking at these past projects and into the future, BBC's Horizon explores science's obsession with the idea of gravity control. Are flying cars and journeys to the stars still the stuff of dreams?

programme.title: Bronson
programme.desc: "In introducing himself, Michael "Charles Bronson" Peterson (Tom Hardy) tells his audience that he sought fame from an early age, but did not have conventional talents. Peterson's early life is shown in flashback, as his violent tendencies begin to surface at school. At the age of 19, his robbery of a post office sends him to prison for seven years, where he comes into his psychopathic element. Creating constant havoc by starting fights with prison officers sees Peterson shunted around various prisons and eventually a psychiatric hospital. He is eventually paroled, and starts boxing, taking on the stage name of Charles Bronson. Inevitably, Bronson ends up back in prison, and notches up 30 years in solitary confinement, which only heightens his distorted and evil take on reality, and ensures his infamy instead of fame."

programme.title: The Nefertiti Bust
programme.desc: This documentary uncovers the extraordinary story behind one of the ancient worlds most iconic images. The blue-crowned statue of a beautiful woman, wearing the full regalia of a royal wife was officially dug out of the Amarna desert in 1912. Since that time, admirers have marvelled not only at its artistry, but at its remarkable preservation: the fact that something so delicate could have survived, virtually pristine, for three and a half thousand years. This program traces the history of the bust, and the woman behind it. Egyptologists Jacquelyn Williamson and Barry Kemp reveal Queen Nefertiti as the most powerful woman that Egypt had known. They uncover a story of political, cultural and religious revolution. (From the UK) G CC

programme.desc: Chef Robert Irvine faces a daunting challenge as he attempts to turn around a failing restaurant in just two days with only $10,000. Although it appears wildly successful, the restaurant is being run into the ground, so the parents have called in Robert Irvine to intervene. He'll have to find out where the money is going, get this restaurant clean and get the brothers to find their drive.
